  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You are inevitable. You gain a +1 bonus on saving throws and to your CMD against effects that would slow or impair your movement (such as entangled, grappled, paralyzed, staggered, or other similar effects), increasing by +1 for every 4 base attack bonus you possess. Whenever you would attempt a save against an effect that would slow or immobilize you, you may roll twice, taking the better result.</p>\n<p>In addition, once per round, you may expend martial focus as an immediate action to attempt a save against an effect which has slowed or impaired your movement, or make a combat maneuver or other appropriate check to escape a grapple, Lancer impale, or other similar effect.</p>\n",
